text: Da Nhay Beach is a beach on the shore of South China Sea. Da Nhay in Vietnamese means the rocks that jump. The beach was called this because of the geographical appearance of it; it has thousands rock reaching the sea and surrounding small fine sand beaches. == Location == It is about 40 km north of Đồng Hới city, Quảng Bình Province, Vietnam. ==Other websites== * Introduction of Da Nhay Beach on Official website of Vietnam Tourism Authority Category:Quảng Bình province Category:Beaches of Asia
title: Đá Nhảy Beach
